JOHANNESBURG - Rand Water on Saturday afternoon said water supply has been restored some areas in Ekurhuleni. Technicians from the metro have been working to restore power at a Rand Water substation this afternoon which affected the distribution of water in the area. Rand Water has cautioned the process will take some time. Spokesperson Edward Spingo said: “We are monitoring the levels of the reservoirs. We are seeing that the areas that are really that are really impacted are in the City of Ekurhuleni.”